---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service - MarkdownMaster"
  description="MarkdownMaster terms of service. Free online Markdown editor terms and conditions."
  canonical="https://markdownmaster.site/terms/"
>
  <style>
    .page-wrap { max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .page-wrap h1 { font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .page-wrap h2 { font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem; color: var(--accent); }
    .page-wrap p { color: #cbd5e1; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    .page-wrap ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; color: #cbd5e1; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    .page-wrap li { margin: 0.3rem 0; }
  </style>

  <div class="page-wrap">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: April 2026</em></p>

    <h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
    <p>By using MarkdownMaster, you agree to these terms of service. If you do not agree, please do not use the service.</p>

    <h2>Free Service</h2>
    <p>MarkdownMaster is provided as a free, open-source tool. We reserve the right to modify or discontinue the service at any time without notice.</p>

    <h2>Use of Service</h2>
    <p>You agree to use MarkdownMaster for lawful purposes only. You may not use the service to generate or distribute harmful, illegal, or abusive content.</p>

    <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p>MarkdownMaster itself is open source. Your content remains your own property. We claim no ownership over the documents you create using the editor.</p>

    <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>MarkdownMaster is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. We are not liable for any damages arising from the use of this service.</p>

    <h2>Changes to Terms</h2>
    <p>We may update these terms at any time. Continued use of the service after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
